# Epic 3: Core URL & Group Management with Basic Iframe Display

## Problem Analysis

- **Goal**: Enable administrators to create, manage, and organize URLs and URL Groups. Enable authenticated users to view their assigned groups/URLs. Implement basic iframe display functionality with appropriate visual indicators and navigation.
- **Key Requirements**:
  - Define core content and access database schemas
  - Create admin APIs for URL and Group management
  - Build admin UIs for managing URLs and Groups
  - Implement user-facing API for personalized content
  - Create global UI components (header, user menu)
  - Build dashboard with iframe display capability

## Current Status

### 2025-05-27 07:40

**Status**: Planned

- What's working: N/A - Planning phase
- What's not: N/A - Not started implementation
- Blocking issues: Epics 1 and 2 need to be completed first
- Next actions: Complete preceding epics, then begin with Story 3.1
- Documentation updates needed:
  - [ ] Database schema documentation for content entities
  - [ ] URL and Group management flows
  - [ ] Iframe handling documentation

## Implementation Steps

- [ ] **Story 3.1: Define Core Content & Access Prisma Schemas**
  - [ ] Update schema.prisma with Url model (including `id`, `originalUrl` (unique), `title` (required), `faviconUrl` (optional), `notes` (optional), `mobileSpecificUrl` (optional), timestamps, and relations)
  - [ ] Add Group model definition (including `id`, `name` (NOT globally unique), `description` (optional), `displayOrder` (optional), timestamps, and relations)
  - [ ] Create UrlInGroup relation model with `@@unique([urlId, groupId])` constraint and appropriate fields (`groupSpecificTitle`, `displayOrderInGroup`)
  - [ ] Define UserGroupAccess relation model with `@@unique([userId, groupId])` constraint
  - [ ] Update User model with necessary relations (`addedUrls`, `createdGroups`, `groupAccesses`)
  - [ ] Implement proper referential actions (`onDelete: SetNull` for creator fields, `onDelete: Cascade` for join tables)
  - [ ] Generate and apply migrations
  - Success criteria: Complete database schema for content entities with appropriate relations
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (User Schema)

- [ ] **Story 3.2: Implement Admin API Endpoints for CRUD Operations on URL Groups**
  - [ ] Create API routes under /api/admin/urlGroups
  - [ ] Implement group creation endpoint (with `name`, `description?`, `displayOrder?`, setting `createdByUserId` to authenticated admin)
  - [ ] Add endpoints for listing, updating, and deleting groups
  - [ ] Ensure proper sorting (displayOrder then name)
  - [ ] Implement cascade deletion for related UrlInGroup and UserGroupAccess entries
  - [ ] Add comprehensive error handling with appropriate HTTP status codes and clear JSON error messages
  - Success criteria: Complete, secure API for group management
  - Dependencies: Story 3.1

- [ ] **Story 3.3: Implement Admin API Endpoints for Global URLs**
  - [ ] Create API routes under /api/admin/urls
  - [ ] Implement URL creation with icon auto-discovery
  - [ ] Implement enhanced icon auto-discovery logic with 3-5 second timeout, prioritizing higher-resolution images
  - [ ] Check for favicons, apple-touch-icons, manifest icons, and Open Graph images during auto-discovery
  - [ ] Skip auto-discovery if `faviconUrl` is manually provided
  - [ ] Store discovered favicon URL in `Url.faviconUrl` (store link, not re-hosted file)
  - [ ] Add endpoints for listing (sorted by `title`), updating, and deleting URLs
  - [ ] Create URL update logic that re-checks for icon on `originalUrl` change (unless explicit `faviconUrl` provided)
  - [ ] Add proper error handling for duplicates (409 status with descriptive message)
  - [ ] Set `addedByUserId` to authenticated admin on creation
  - Success criteria: Complete API for global URL management with icon discovery
  - Dependencies: Story 3.1

- [ ] **Story 3.4: Implement Admin API Endpoints for Managing URLs within Groups**
  - [ ] Create nested API routes for URL-in-Group operations
  - [ ] Implement adding URLs to groups with validation for existing group and URL
  - [ ] Add endpoints for listing, updating, and removing URLs from groups
  - [ ] Ensure proper sorting by displayOrderInGroup
  - [ ] Add comprehensive error handling including unique constraint violations
  - [ ] Ensure deletion does not remove the global URL or group, only the association
  - Success criteria: Complete API for managing URL membership in groups
  - Dependencies: Stories 3.2, 3.3

- [ ] **Story 3.5: Develop Admin UI for URL Group Management**
  - [ ] Create group management page at `/admin/url-groups`
  - [ ] Implement group listing with sorting (displayOrder then name)
  - [ ] Add UI for creating, editing, and deleting groups
  - [ ] Include confirmation dialogs with clear warnings about cascade deletion effects
  - [ ] Add links/actions to manage URLs within each group (leads to Story 3.6 UI)
  - [ ] Connect to APIs from Story 3.2
  - [ ] Implement consistent MUI components with loading indicators and feedback
  - Success criteria: Functional UI for group management
  - Dependencies: Stories 2.1, 3.2

- [ ] **Story 3.6: Develop Admin UI for Managing URLs within Groups**
  - [ ] Create URL-in-Group management UI at `/admin/url-groups/[groupId]/urls`
  - [ ] Implement listing URLs in selected group (sorted by displayOrderInGroup)
  - [ ] Add UI for adding global URLs to group (searchable selector, options for initial displayOrderInGroup and groupSpecificTitle)
  - [ ] Create UI for reordering (drag-and-drop or Up/Down buttons) and editing group-specific properties
  - [ ] Add UI for removing URLs from group with confirmation ("does not delete global URL")
  - [ ] Connect to APIs from Story 3.4
  - [ ] Add easy navigation back to main group management
  - Success criteria: Functional UI for managing URLs within groups
  - Dependencies: Stories 3.4, 3.5

- [ ] **Story 3.6.5: Develop Admin UI for Global URL Management**
  - [ ] Create global URL management page at `/admin/global-urls`
  - [ ] Implement URL listing with sorting by title
  - [ ] Add UI for creating, editing, and deleting global URLs
  - [ ] Create favicon management UI with auto-discovery feedback
  - [ ] Implement file upload for custom icons (JPG/PNG/ICO, max 100KB) to `/public/url_favicons/`
  - [ ] Add UI options to "Upload Custom Icon", "Re-check for Auto-Discovered Icon", and "Remove Icon"
  - [ ] Implement proper handling of duplicate `originalUrl` errors ("Error: URL exists as '[Existing Title]'...")
  - [ ] Add confirmation dialogs for deletions with warnings about removal from all groups
  - [ ] Connect to APIs from Story 3.3
  - Success criteria: Functional UI for global URL management
  - Dependencies: Stories 2.1, 3.3

- [ ] **Story 3.7: Implement API for Users to Fetch Their Accessible Groups and URLs**
  - [ ] Create API endpoint for authenticated users at `/api/dashboard/urlGroups`
  - [ ] Implement data fetching for user-accessible groups through UserGroupAccess
  - [ ] Add proper data structure with effective titles (UrlInGroup.groupSpecificTitle or Url.title)
  - [ ] Ensure all dates are formatted as ISO strings in JSON response
  - [ ] Return groups sorted by displayOrder then name, with URLs sorted by displayOrderInGroup
  - [ ] Optimize database queries to minimize database round-trips
  - Success criteria: API returns personalized content for users
  - Dependencies: Story 3.1

- [ ] **Story 3.8: Implement Global User Menu and Application Header**
  - [ ] Create AppBar component with conditional display (always on mobile, only when menuPosition=TOP on desktop)
  - [ ] Implement three-section structure for TOP menu: Logo/Name (Left), Central Area for Navigation (Center-Left), User Menu Button (Right)
  - [ ] Implement User Menu dropdown with Dashboard, Settings, Admin links (conditional), Theme Toggle, and Logout
  - [ ] Add theme toggle functionality with persisted preferences
  - [ ] Create mobile hamburger menu that toggles drawer navigation
  - [ ] Ensure responsive design with appropriate layout changes for different screen sizes
  - Success criteria: Consistent header with user menu across application
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (Authentication)

- [ ] **Story 3.9: Implement User Dashboard UI with Multi-Iframe Handling**
  - [ ] Create dashboard page with data fetching from Story 3.7
  - [ ] Implement mobile drawer navigation (accordion groups/URLs, selected group expanded by default)
  - [ ] Ensure selecting a URL closes the mobile drawer
  - [ ] Add URL item visual states:
    - [ ] Non-active/non-loaded URLs: opacity 0.5
    - [ ] Non-active/loaded URLs: opacity 1.0
    - [ ] Active/loaded URLs: opacity 1.0 + blue underline (Top Menu) or blue right border (Side Menu & Mobile Drawer)
  - [ ] Create multi-iframe management system:
    - [ ] One iframe per unique URL kept in DOM
    - [ ] Use visibility:hidden and position:absolute for inactive iframes to preserve state
    - [ ] Add proper sandbox attributes: `allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-forms allow-downloads allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox`
  - [ ] Implement initial iframe loading (first URL of first group)
  - [ ] Add group state persistence during current session
  - [ ] Handle broken favicons gracefully by showing title prominently
  - [ ] Ensure main layout fits 100% viewport height, no main scrollbars
  - Success criteria: Functional dashboard displaying URLs in iframes with state indicators
  - Dependencies: Stories 3.7, 3.8

## Affected Components

- Database schema (Prisma)
- Admin API endpoints
- Admin UI for URL and Group management
- User-facing API for personalized content
- Global header and navigation components
- Dashboard with iframe display

## Dependencies

- Epic 1 (Authentication, User Schema)
- Epic 2 (Admin Dashboard Layout)
- Material UI v6
- Prisma ORM

## Technical Considerations

- Iframe security requires proper sandbox attributes (`allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-forms allow-downloads allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox`)
- State preservation between iframe switching needs careful implementation using CSS visibility and positioning
- Icon auto-discovery requires robust error handling with reasonable timeouts (3-5 seconds)
- Proper error handling for unique constraints in database
- Performance optimization for user content fetching
- File storage paths: favicon files should be stored in `/public/url_favicons/`

